<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="464" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Prell, 1913" authorityName=", Prell Determined" authorityYear="1913" box="[325,693,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[325,558,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">Eophileurus gracilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Prell, H." box="[567,693,151,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" pagination="103 - 124" refId="ref17521" refString="Prell, H. (1913) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Dynastinen. viii. Ueber das Genus Eophilurus Arrow. Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 22, 103 - 124." type="journal article" year="1913">Prell, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Andaman Island. 
<taxonomicName authority="Arrow, 1914" authorityName="Arrow" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andamanicus">
<emphasis box="[1140,1436,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">Eophileurus andamanicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Arrow, G. J." box="[151,295,187,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" pagination="257 - 276" refId="ref16776" refString="Arrow, G. J. (1914) Some further notes on Lamellicorn beetles of the sub-family Dynastinae. The Annals and Magazine of natural History, including Zoology, Botany and Geology, 8 (14), 257 - 276. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931408693571" type="journal article" year="1914">Arrow, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Andaman Island and Nicobar Island by 
<bibRefCitation author="Arrow, G. J." box="[1001,1159,187,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" pagination="257 - 276" refId="ref16776" refString="Arrow, G. J. (1914) Some further notes on Lamellicorn beetles of the sub-family Dynastinae. The Annals and Magazine of natural History, including Zoology, Botany and Geology, 8 (14), 257 - 276. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931408693571" type="journal article" year="1914">Arrow (1914)</bibRefCitation>
without mentioning the species described by Prell one year prior, it is then treated as junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Prell Determined" authorityYear="1913" box="[1088,1208,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[1088,1208,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">E. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Endrodi, S." box="[1255,1433,222,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" refId="ref17001" refString="Endrodi, S. (1985) The Dynastinae of the World. W. Junk, Dordrecht, 800 pp." type="book" year="1985">Endrődi (1985)</bibRefCitation>
. By examining the type material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Prell Determined" authorityYear="1913" box="[553,672,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[553,672,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">E. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[688,825,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–59" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[158,1426,643,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-215@12.[151,1435,633,1909]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 54–59. Lectotype of Eophileurus gracilis Prell, 1913. 54, habitus, dorsal; 55, habitus, lateral; 56, habitus, ventral; 57, parameres, apical; 58, parameres, lateral; 59, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853960/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">Figs. 54–59</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Arrow" authorityYear="1914" box="[891,1073,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andamanicus">
<emphasis box="[891,1073,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">E. andamanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1090,1229,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 60–64" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1304,1328]" captionTargetBox="[159,1434,424,1278]" captionTargetId="figure-125@13.[151,1435,417,1280]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 60–64. Lectotype of Eophileurus andamanicus Arrow, 1914 (images by Keita Matsumoto © Natural History Museum, London). 60, habitus, dorsal; 61, habitus, lateral; 62, parameres, apical; 63, parameres, lateral; 64, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853962/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">Figs. 60–64</figureCitation>
), the treatment by Endrődi is considered valid. 
<typeStatus box="[479,591,295,321]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Arrow" authorityYear="1914" box="[631,813,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andamanicus">
<emphasis box="[631,813,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">E. andamanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is designated for the only 
<typeStatus box="[1120,1207,295,321]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">syntype</typeStatus>
originally dissected by Arrow. The 
<typeStatus box="[319,470,331,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">paralectotype</typeStatus>
from Nicobar Island was dissected by Keita Matsumoto (BMNH) and confirmed to be conspecific, thus confirming its distribution on Nicobar Island.
</paragraph>
